    dc:creator "Marin, Carlos M.; Molina-Zuluaga, Claudia; Restrepo, Adriana; Cano, Estefany; Daza, Juan M." ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Leucostethus (Anura: Dendrobatidae) from the eastern versant of the Central Cordillera of Colombia and the phylogenetic status of Colostethus fraterdanieli" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460125>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460127>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460131>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460123>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460129>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460133>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460135>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460137>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460139>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460141> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460125>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Holotype of Leucostethus jota sp. nov. adult male MHUA-A 8138 in life. SVL 19.32 mm. Photo by Juan M. Daza." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460125/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460127>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Foot and hand morphology of Leucostethus jota sp. nov. A) Right foot of adult male holotype MHUA-A 8138. Foot length = 8.8 mm). B) Right hand of adult male holotype showing swelling along the preaxial side of finger III. Hand length = 5.2 mm. C) Right hand of adult female paratype MHUA-A 8137. Hand length = 5.1 mm. Finger III not swollen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460127/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460131>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Holotype of Leucostethus jota sp. nov. in preservative (MHUA-A 8138). SVL 19.3 mm. (A) Lateral view. (B) Ventral view. (C) Dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460131/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460123>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood tree (-lnL=120317.99) depicting evolutionary relationships within Colostethinae inferred from a partitioned analysis using 11978 characters, 16 genomic regions, and 183 terminals. Colored symbols next to the clades are represented as point localities in figure 10." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460123/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460129>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Testes color in (A) Leucostethus fraterdanieli (MHUA-A 8176) and (B) Leucostethus jota sp. nov. (MHUA-A 9534). Arrows indicate testes position." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460129/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460133>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Spectrogram and oscillogram of the advertisement call of two species: A) Single pulse and B) multiple pulses of Leucostethus fraterdanieli (MHUA-A 8176). C) Single pulse and D) multiple pulses of Leucostethus jota sp. nov. (MHUA-A 9533). Note the higher frequency and lower call rate in L. jota sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460133/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460135>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. PCA plot of bioacoustic parameters from L. jota sp. nov. and L. fraterdanieli. PCA was performed with 3 spectral parameters (Low frequency, High frequency and Peak frequency) and 1 temporal parameter (Call duration)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460135/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460137>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Acoustic activity in a population of Leucostethus jota sp. nov. inferred from 27788 calls, obtained during November-December 2012 and January through September 2014 in the municipality of Alejandría, Antioquia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460137/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460139>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Leucostethus jota sp. nov. A) Vocalizing male; uncollected specimen B) Adult male carrying tadpoles; uncollected specimens. Photos by Juan M. Daza." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460139/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1460141>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Geographic distribution of sequenced specimens of Leucostethus jota sp. nov. and Leucostethus fraterdanieli “complex” in Colombia. Colored symbols represent the clades shown in figure 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1460141/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

